hopobject.body: Have you read any good books lately? lopressor cvs For quick photos, the Moto X will pull up the camera app with two twists of the wrist. Flick your wrist to the left or right twice and the camera appears without the need to enter a passcode, allowing you to take pics in less than two seconds, Motorola said. The feature worked well enough, though you might feel a little dumb flicking your phone around - especially if it doesn't work on the first take. It reminded me a bit of "shake to shuffle" on iOS, which I quickly disabled after my iPod would change songs as I walked.
